<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Belinar on 06-11-2001 03:02 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I have a question that I posted earlier (alot earlier, before the beta emu) and would like to re-itterate the possibility of a working version of this utility being that a_necro has graciously posted some kind of update. (not bashing Ash here, he's busy...I'm just happy to hear a 70% done)

Idea is - proggy that will capture spawn points, what the random chance for loot off mobs is, what the item/s are. Something you would run in the background like the item collector that not only collects items, but "spawn points, the random chance of a mob having an item, what the item is, etc" so you can run around EC, gather the info, and just copy the file to a directory in the emu called "East_Commonlands" and the file would be called "ecommons.zne" or something, whatever the emu format is, and use that as the populated zone...

You may even be able to go so far as hailing npc's and gathering quest info that is sent to the client. 

I understand that much if not all of the random checks for items and such are done serverside, but if "anything" is sent to the client, grab it.

I also understand that ShowEQ does almost the exact thing I'm suggesting... ***BUT***, get it to dump the info in a file in such a way that it's usable w/ the emu. if we have that, it'd be easy for us to make Verant-like clones of the actual servers, and then go back and fix what we want...no time consuming "make crap_npc_vendor00...give crap_npc_vendor00 #item 123* or whatever you'll have to do...the proggy will do that for you. just click on the vendor.

Not really sure if it's possible, but I figured I'd re-ask, being I didn't get a very satisfactory answer before...and I understand why...we didn't have the knowledge...we really don't now, but if you know how to use ShowEQ, or have helped work on it, perhaps it's possible to make zone files that will either
1. work on the emu
2. look good, and maybe with a little tweaking work on the emu
3. at least give the ppl the info they need (IE loc's of npc spawns, vendors, etc) to do it fast and efficiently.

Just an idea, anyway. =)

..."Live to play, or get out of the way!!!"...


</TEXTAREA>
